      "id": 1,
      "text": "New Milford became a borough in 1922 when Peetzburg, New Milford Manor, and New Bridge merged.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.britannica.com/place/New-Milford-New-Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The borough was named for Samuel Fleming, a prominent early settler in the 18th century.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flemington%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Settlements like Peetzburg and New Milford emerged along rail corridors, turning isolated farms into nucleated villages.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/New_Milford,_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Hunterdon County Courthouse, where the Lindbergh Trial unfolded, stands as a historic landmark.",
